  "prompt": "What should the purpose of your life?",
  "response": "Determining the purpose of one's life is deeply personal and can vary greatly from person to person. It often involves reflecting on your values, passions, experiences, and beliefs. Here are some steps to help you discover and define your life's purpose:\n\n1. **Self-Reflection:** Spend time thinking about what truly matters to you, what brings you joy, and what you want to achieve. Journaling, meditation, or discussing with trusted friends or mentors can aid in this process.\n\n2. **Identify Strengths and Passions:** Consider what you are good at and what you love to do. Your talents and interests can provide clues to your purpose.\n\n3. **Set Goals:** Define what success means to you and set both short-term and long-term goals that align with your values and aspirations.\n\n4. **Find Meaning:** Seek activities, relationships, and careers that provide a sense of fulfillment and meaning. Often, contributing to the well-being of others or to a cause larger than yourself can enhance your sense of purpose.\n\n5. **Be Open to Change:** Your purpose may evolve over time. Be willing to re-evaluate and adjust your path as you grow and encounter new experiences.\n\nRemember, the purpose of life is not a one-size-fits-all concept; it's a unique journey for everyone.",
